cs.PERF, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.SYSCONF. 

The paper focuses on a tool for performance debugging, which suggests it belongs to the cs.PERF sub-category. It also deals with memory usage, which is a common concern in software engineering, making cs.SE a likely sub-category as well. The tool is specifically designed for Valgrind, a popular dynamic analyzer, which suggests it could also belong to the cs.PL (programming languages) sub-category. The paper also discusses limitations and trade-offs of the tool, which could fall under the cs.AR (architecture) sub-category. Finally, the tool measures memory usage, which is a system-level concern, making cs.SYSCONF a possible sub-category as well.
